50|$|The Senate Standing Committee On <b>Official</b> <b>languages</b> (OLLO) is a {{standing}} {{committee of the}} Senate of Canada responsible for examining issues of Francophone culture in Canada, especially {{in regard to the}} <b>Official</b> <b>Languages</b> Act. It is mandated to study, as the Senate may decide, bills, messages, petitions, inquiries, papers and other matters relating to Canada's <b>official</b> <b>languages</b> generally.|$|R
